1
00:00:09,565 --> 00:00:14,285
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language)

2
00:00:14,285 --> 00:00:20,092
(All characters, places, and events
in this series are entirely fictitious)

3
00:00:20,248 --> 00:00:25,138
=Love of Silom=

4
00:00:26,334 --> 00:00:28,508
(One month later)

5
00:00:28,508 --> 00:00:29,160
Hello, Captain.

6
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:42,871
How's it going, Lieutenant?

7
00:00:43,368 --> 00:00:44,626
We found three bodies.

8
00:00:44,626 --> 00:00:47,142
Forensics is doing
a preliminary exam now.

9
00:00:47,592 --> 00:00:48,539
But, Captain...

10
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:51,636
All three bodies
had their organs removed.

11
00:00:52,405 --> 00:00:55,185
Just like Por's previous victims.

12
00:00:59,797 --> 00:01:01,380
Por had someone backing him.

13
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:05,790
Then have the autopsy rushed.

14
00:01:06,241 --> 00:01:08,073
And confirm the victims' identities.

15
00:01:08,244 --> 00:01:10,200
See if they match
any missing persons reports.

16
00:01:10,324 --> 00:01:11,256
Yes, Captain.

17
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:23,616
Mom, I'm off.

18
00:01:24,610 --> 00:01:26,116
- Oh.
- Oh, there's food too?

19
00:01:26,396 --> 00:01:29,206
Eat first. Come sit down.
I'll serve you. Come on.

20
00:01:29,517 --> 00:01:30,774
- Okay?
- Okay.

21
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:34,874
Aren't you eating, Mom?
Let's eat together.

22
00:01:35,215 --> 00:01:37,405
I've already eaten. I ate since morning.

23
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:41,613
Here, it's still hot.

24
00:01:42,389 --> 00:01:43,600
Mm.

25
00:01:47,529 --> 00:01:48,212
Here.

26
00:01:49,050 --> 00:01:51,457
- You eat. Go on.
- Thank you.

27
00:01:52,762 --> 00:01:56,302
I still have packing to finish.
The courier's coming at 9 AM.

28
00:01:56,675 --> 00:01:57,979
- Mm.
- Eat up.

29
00:01:59,407 --> 00:02:00,060
Ouch.

30
00:02:01,721 --> 00:02:03,041
Got a lot of orders, Wai?

31
00:02:03,196 --> 00:02:05,432
- Mm.
- Why not hire more people?

32
00:02:05,681 --> 00:02:08,833
I've thought about it, but let me
get through this month first.

33
00:02:15,913 --> 00:02:18,056
You were livestreaming
till morning again, weren't you?

34
00:02:18,056 --> 00:02:20,246
Yeah. What else can I do?

35
00:02:20,277 --> 00:02:22,482
Singto's about to start kindergarten.

36
00:02:22,575 --> 00:02:24,345
Expenses are increasing.

37
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:27,808
Luckily, this school has a psychologist.

38
00:02:27,808 --> 00:02:31,720
Otherwise, he might have been delayed
for another year or two.

39
00:02:33,475 --> 00:02:36,487
But there's no fee
for a psychologist, right?

40
00:02:36,814 --> 00:02:40,338
Yes, but the money we have
is still all used up.

41
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:42,497
I can't see any savings at all.

42
00:02:42,730 --> 00:02:45,509
- I'll be live streaming again around noon.
- Mm.

43
00:02:50,431 --> 00:02:54,267
Then get some sleep today.
I'll take Singto to school.

44
00:02:54,453 --> 00:02:56,270
Don't you have class?

45
00:02:56,705 --> 00:02:58,459
I do, but I can drop him off first.

46
00:02:59,189 --> 00:03:00,245
Really?

47
00:03:03,149 --> 00:03:05,322
Okay, thanks. But this evening,

48
00:03:05,322 --> 00:03:06,332
I'll pick him up myself.

49
00:03:06,984 --> 00:03:08,677
- Okay.
- Singto.

50
00:03:08,996 --> 00:03:10,996
You're going to school with Dad today.

51
00:03:12,046 --> 00:03:14,406
Going with Dad today, okay?

52
00:03:14,841 --> 00:03:17,946
Come on, eat your food. Hurry up.

53
00:03:17,946 --> 00:03:19,810
Eat first so we can get going, okay?

54
00:03:19,810 --> 00:03:24,949
- Open up.
- Oh, that's a big bite! Well done!

55
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:27,216
- Well done.
- Show-off.

56
00:03:27,216 --> 00:03:30,586
Such a show-off. I told him back then,
but he wouldn't listen.

57
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:33,257
Hey, let you know

58
00:03:33,257 --> 00:03:35,587
who his real parent is.

59
00:03:35,587 --> 00:03:36,702
Right, Singto?

60
00:03:36,921 --> 00:03:37,651
Right?

61
00:03:37,853 --> 00:03:39,576
- Right?
- Right.

62
00:03:39,654 --> 00:03:42,170
- Eat up.
- One more big bite?

63
00:03:42,170 --> 00:03:43,816
One more big bite? Just one more?

64
00:03:44,328 --> 00:03:47,356
Hello. Well done, Singto.

65
00:03:48,210 --> 00:03:50,197
Wai will pick him up this evening, okay?

66
00:03:50,197 --> 00:03:53,536
Understood. Come on, let's go to class.

67
00:03:54,592 --> 00:03:57,620
- Bye-bye.
- Say bye to Dad first.

68
00:03:57,620 --> 00:03:59,095
Bye-bye.

69
00:03:59,130 --> 00:04:01,766
Singto, come play with me.

70
00:04:07,309 --> 00:04:10,352
(Mind)

71
00:04:10,787 --> 00:04:11,750
Hello, Mind.

72
00:04:12,154 --> 00:04:15,228
Where are you? You're not at campus yet?
I haven't seen you.

73
00:04:15,445 --> 00:04:17,976
I stopped by to drop Singto off
at daycare. I'll hurry over.

74
00:04:18,861 --> 00:04:19,560
Okay.

75
00:04:43,085 --> 00:04:45,367
Singto talks to his friends more.

76
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:46,827
Even if he's not fluent yet,

77
00:04:46,827 --> 00:04:50,103
he's still trying to communicate
in his own way.

78
00:04:51,361 --> 00:04:54,684
Singto is making good progress, though
he's still a bit behind other kids.

79
00:04:54,684 --> 00:04:57,696
If he keeps opening up,
he'll definitely catch up.

80
00:04:57,696 --> 00:05:00,088
And eventually, he'll be speaking
normally like the other children.

81
00:05:03,395 --> 00:05:07,090
Thank you so much,
for always looking out for him.

82
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:10,615
Actually, you should tell
Mr. Wayu and Ms. Wai, Captain,

83
00:05:10,615 --> 00:05:13,022
that you're the one
who's always helping out.

84
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:15,491
Their family should be thankful to you.

85
00:05:20,491 --> 00:05:24,031
Please keep helping to encourage Singto
with his pronunciation.

86
00:05:24,031 --> 00:05:25,832
Help him feel more confident
when he speaks.

87
00:05:25,832 --> 00:05:27,820
So he knows he's getting better
every single day.

88
00:05:28,348 --> 00:05:29,031
Of course.

89
00:05:42,183 --> 00:05:44,450
Thanks a lot for taking care
of all this.

90
00:05:45,133 --> 00:05:46,624
When Singto can speak,

91
00:05:47,167 --> 00:05:49,216
- I owe you big time.
- Hmm.

92
00:05:50,382 --> 00:05:53,083
You're just like Rose said, really.

93
00:05:53,798 --> 00:05:54,574
How so?

94
00:05:55,304 --> 00:05:59,496
You even hired me to stay close
and look after your ex's nephew.

95
00:06:00,133 --> 00:06:01,779
Why are you putting yourself
through this?

96
00:06:01,888 --> 00:06:04,139
Why not just get back together
and settle it once and for all?

97
00:06:05,412 --> 00:06:07,089
Has anyone ever told you this?

98
00:06:07,089 --> 00:06:11,096
Watching over him from a distance
like this, without letting him know,

99
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:13,689
is not cool. It's just sad.

100
00:06:15,863 --> 00:06:17,804
I'm just doing what I said I would.

101
00:06:18,984 --> 00:06:21,996
I told him I'd look after Singto.
That's all.

102
00:06:22,213 --> 00:06:25,350
Yeah. Everyone knows what you should do.

103
00:06:25,567 --> 00:06:26,916
But you won't do it.

104
00:06:28,533 --> 00:06:31,747
I'm heading back to the kids.
You should get back to work.

105
00:06:32,974 --> 00:06:34,341
- Thanks.
- Mm.

106
00:06:43,393 --> 00:06:44,791
Dad cried.

107
00:06:45,769 --> 00:06:46,607
What?

108
00:06:47,478 --> 00:06:48,892
Dad cried.

109
00:06:49,340 --> 00:06:51,483
Did Dad cry?

110
00:06:58,905 --> 00:06:59,915
It's okay.

111
00:07:01,793 --> 00:07:04,324
Singto, you have to be a good boy,
alright? Hmm?

112
00:07:05,970 --> 00:07:07,228
You have to be strong.

113
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:09,309
Okay?

114
00:07:12,601 --> 00:07:14,402
You have grown a lot
since the last time I saw you.

115
00:07:15,629 --> 00:07:17,709
You're talking more too. Hmm?

116
00:07:18,719 --> 00:07:19,961
Oh.

117
00:07:35,784 --> 00:07:36,374
Ouch.

118
00:07:36,995 --> 00:07:40,530
- Mind, hey, did the cutter cut you?
- Yeah.

119
00:07:40,908 --> 00:07:45,364
Mind, I told you I could handle it.
But you had to butt in anyway.

120
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:47,709
You're complaining
even though I came to help?

121
00:07:50,675 --> 00:07:53,656
Who told you to help
till you got yourself hurt?

122
00:07:54,386 --> 00:07:56,249
Hey, look at this.

123
00:07:56,420 --> 00:07:58,796
- Whoa, my model is stained with blood.
- Oh.

124
00:07:59,463 --> 00:08:01,063
Worry about me, not the model.

125
00:08:01,932 --> 00:08:03,516
I am worried.

126
00:08:04,338 --> 00:08:06,675
But if you're going to help,
be more careful, okay?

127
00:08:07,289 --> 00:08:09,246
Next time, just sit still,
that's enough.

128
00:08:10,364 --> 00:08:11,342
Keep pressure on it for now.

129
00:08:14,882 --> 00:08:15,488
Come on.

130
00:08:22,879 --> 00:08:26,621
Aww, what a sweet model cutting!

131
00:08:26,621 --> 00:08:29,059
Should I make this
your relationship reveal clip?

132
00:08:29,075 --> 00:08:31,404
Sweet.

133
00:08:31,637 --> 00:08:33,003
We're just friends.

134
00:08:33,174 --> 00:08:35,783
Hmm.

135
00:08:36,776 --> 00:08:37,646
What?

136
00:08:38,422 --> 00:08:40,363
That's enough. You don't have
to do it anymore. I'll handle it.

137
00:08:41,186 --> 00:08:42,040
Mm.

138
00:08:53,361 --> 00:08:54,354
I'm heading out first, Wayu.

139
00:09:30,487 --> 00:09:34,244
(Hurry up and come help design my house.)

140
00:09:34,617 --> 00:09:36,620
Wayu, what are you doing?

141
00:09:37,459 --> 00:09:40,052
Slicing. Slicing the model.

142
00:09:40,052 --> 00:09:42,738
- Slicing the model. We use "slice"?
- Yep.

143
00:09:57,194 --> 00:09:59,353
Mind.

144
00:09:59,508 --> 00:10:01,216
Wake up. Let's go home.

145
00:10:02,474 --> 00:10:04,989
What else do you need help?

146
00:10:05,626 --> 00:10:07,458
Oh, that's enough for today.

147
00:10:07,551 --> 00:10:09,601
I'll take the rest home
and finish it there.

148
00:10:10,284 --> 00:10:12,380
Okay, I'll get you home.

149
00:10:13,467 --> 00:10:16,480
It's fine. You've been helping me
cut the model for days.

150
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:17,735
You should head back and get some rest.

151
00:10:18,436 --> 00:10:19,523
If you feel bad,

152
00:10:20,563 --> 00:10:21,433
make it up to me.

153
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:25,610
How to?

154
00:10:26,635 --> 00:10:28,312
Take me out somewhere.

155
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,392
Somewhere off campus.

156
00:10:31,246 --> 00:10:34,694
Oh, but not drinking.
I don't want to drink.

157
00:10:34,725 --> 00:10:36,945
I never said anything about drinking.

158
00:10:37,116 --> 00:10:40,051
Just hanging out,
like normal college kids.

159
00:10:43,374 --> 00:10:46,805
Okay? Think of it as a break.

160
00:10:50,516 --> 00:10:52,178
Ah, alright then.

161
00:10:52,706 --> 00:10:56,091
Okay, let's go home.

162
00:10:57,209 --> 00:10:59,227
- Let's go home.
- Let's go.

163
00:11:00,376 --> 00:11:01,525
You said it already.

164
00:11:05,159 --> 00:11:06,618
Whoa, Mind.

165
00:11:07,038 --> 00:11:09,817
Is jogging a trip now too?

166
00:11:09,817 --> 00:11:11,059
That's news to me.

167
00:11:11,510 --> 00:11:12,985
It's for health, you know.

168
00:11:13,684 --> 00:11:16,836
But a muscular guy
like Wayu should be fine, right?

169
00:11:17,239 --> 00:11:18,885
Don't hosts have to stay in shape?

170
00:11:19,398 --> 00:11:21,121
- Wow.
- Give it a rest.

171
00:11:21,121 --> 00:11:24,180
I haven't worked out at all
since school started, so...

172
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,055
This is what I look like now.

173
00:11:27,363 --> 00:11:30,298
Even like this, you still look good.

174
00:11:30,531 --> 00:11:32,907
Wow, hardcore stanning.

175
00:11:41,121 --> 00:11:41,882
Thanks.

176
00:11:51,338 --> 00:11:52,844
(Don't worry.)

177
00:11:53,015 --> 00:11:54,490
I'll take care of you and Singto.

178
00:12:06,788 --> 00:12:07,518
Wayu.

179
00:12:09,428 --> 00:12:12,363
Want to hit an onsen or sauna?
You'll feel better.

180
00:12:21,990 --> 00:12:23,108
Sorry, Mind, it's just...

181
00:12:24,288 --> 00:12:26,089
I'm not really into saunas.

182
00:12:26,089 --> 00:12:29,288
Oh. Then want to grab food instead?

183
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:31,633
Okay.

184
00:12:32,688 --> 00:12:34,039
- Hello.
- Hello.

185
00:12:34,039 --> 00:12:35,049
- You're Mr. Mind, right?
- Yes, I am.

186
00:12:35,049 --> 00:12:36,089
Please come this way.

187
00:12:39,412 --> 00:12:40,406
This way, please.

188
00:12:52,828 --> 00:12:53,558
Wayu.

189
00:12:54,924 --> 00:12:55,530
Wayu.

190
00:12:57,098 --> 00:12:57,921
Are you okay?

191
00:12:59,303 --> 00:13:02,393
Hey, if you don't like it,
we can change the restaurant.

192
00:13:03,169 --> 00:13:04,567
Ooh, it's okay, Mind.

193
00:13:05,328 --> 00:13:06,166
Just...

194
00:13:06,977 --> 00:13:09,862
I didn't know it was this place,
so I didn't prepare.

195
00:13:11,073 --> 00:13:13,650
Even though you didn't prepare,

196
00:13:14,629 --> 00:13:15,591
you look good already.

197
00:13:16,181 --> 00:13:18,309
- Let's eat then.
- Let's go.

198
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:23,852
This table here, Mr. Mind.

199
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:28,930
- May I change tables, please?
- Sure.

200
00:13:30,110 --> 00:13:31,041
This table is fine too.

201
00:13:31,399 --> 00:13:32,982
Yes, here you go.

202
00:13:34,566 --> 00:13:36,662
- Do you prefer this table?
- Yeah.

203
00:13:45,684 --> 00:13:46,507
Are you hungry yet?

204
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:49,737
- A little.
- Here's the menu.

205
00:13:49,737 --> 00:13:51,305
- Thank you.
- The menu, please.

206
00:13:51,305 --> 00:13:52,190
Thank you.

207
00:14:16,739 --> 00:14:17,500
(Wayu.)

208
00:14:18,354 --> 00:14:20,482
- Wayu.
- Huh?

209
00:14:21,118 --> 00:14:22,438
Have you decided?
What do you want to eat?

210
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:26,475
Oh, give me a second.

211
00:14:33,012 --> 00:14:35,745
- Mind, you ready?
- Yeah. Here.

212
00:14:37,096 --> 00:14:38,882
Then I'll have the same as you, Mind.

213
00:14:39,270 --> 00:14:40,543
- The exact same?
- Yeah.

214
00:14:42,795 --> 00:14:45,854
I'll have Bistecca alla Fiorentina.
Two servings, please.

215
00:14:45,854 --> 00:14:47,857
- Of course.
- Thank you.

216
00:14:51,879 --> 00:14:54,829
So, what's up with you today, Wayu?

217
00:14:55,792 --> 00:14:57,049
You don't look too good.

218
00:14:59,177 --> 00:14:59,984
No.

219
00:15:00,217 --> 00:15:02,033
- No?
- Yeah, nothing's wrong.

220
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:03,198
- Really?
- Mmm.

221
00:15:03,198 --> 00:15:04,378
- Really?
- Mmm-hmm.

222
00:15:04,534 --> 00:15:05,357
Are you sure?

223
00:15:07,919 --> 00:15:09,689
- Hey, Mind, did you know?
- Huh?

224
00:15:09,689 --> 00:15:11,599
I used to work part-time here.

225
00:15:11,878 --> 00:15:12,934
- Really?
- Mm.

226
00:15:12,934 --> 00:15:15,992
So did you know that server just now?

227
00:15:17,064 --> 00:15:19,906
Hmm... But looks like they've got
a whole new staff now.

228
00:15:19,906 --> 00:15:22,530
Ah, I see.

229
00:15:25,061 --> 00:15:27,452
Hey, Mind, I told you...

230
00:15:27,452 --> 00:15:30,216
You didn't have to do this. I would've
been happy with some street food,

231
00:15:30,216 --> 00:15:32,592
- Noodles would've filled me up too.
- Well.

232
00:15:32,639 --> 00:15:34,983
The noodle shop? By campus
would've been fine too, right?

233
00:15:36,163 --> 00:15:39,549
I told you, Wayu. I just wanted
to get off campus for once.

234
00:15:40,713 --> 00:15:41,552
Mm.

235
00:15:42,406 --> 00:15:44,362
- And what's this, huh?
- Hmm?

236
00:15:44,828 --> 00:15:47,297
You got all dressed up
and didn't even tell me first.

237
00:15:49,859 --> 00:15:51,194
I always look this good, don't I?

238
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:54,999
This looks good too. I mean your outfit.

239
00:15:55,868 --> 00:15:57,825
I always dress well, don't I?

240
00:16:00,309 --> 00:16:01,272
True.

241
00:16:04,921 --> 00:16:07,203
- Excuse me, may I serve this?
- Thank you.

242
00:16:08,849 --> 00:16:10,619
So? Does it look good?

243
00:16:10,883 --> 00:16:13,336
It looks amazing. And so pretty too.

244
00:16:14,424 --> 00:16:15,324
Let's take a picture first.

245
00:16:38,445 --> 00:16:39,687
- Wayu.
- Hmm?

246
00:16:41,147 --> 00:16:42,032
Give me your hand.

247
00:16:44,811 --> 00:16:47,016
Why are you asking? Huh, I'm not a dog.

248
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:48,926
Come on. Give me your hand.

249
00:16:52,994 --> 00:16:55,541
What? Are you giving me a gift?
I'm not taking it.

250
00:16:56,255 --> 00:16:57,606
Can you just pretend
you don't know for once?

251
00:16:58,507 --> 00:16:59,842
Nope.

252
00:17:00,681 --> 00:17:03,879
We're just friends. You can't give me
a gift. It's not even my birthday.

253
00:17:03,988 --> 00:17:04,858
Yeah.

254
00:17:05,634 --> 00:17:07,699
I know you don't like
expensive things, Wayu.

255
00:17:08,957 --> 00:17:09,951
So I made it myself.

256
00:17:10,572 --> 00:17:12,249
- Really?
- Hand over your hand.

257
00:17:14,081 --> 00:17:14,920
Come on. Give it here.

258
00:17:16,597 --> 00:17:17,249
Here.

259
00:17:20,183 --> 00:17:22,031
- Wow.
- It fits perfectly.

260
00:17:22,683 --> 00:17:23,367
See?

261
00:17:24,439 --> 00:17:25,991
You made this yourself?

262
00:17:26,395 --> 00:17:29,081
Yeah, I took a workshop for it.

263
00:17:30,432 --> 00:17:33,584
I think maybe...

264
00:17:35,028 --> 00:17:36,472
Maybe it's time.

265
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:40,820
Time for you
to finally let go of the past.

266
00:17:42,310 --> 00:17:46,053
And give yourself
a real chance to be happy.

267
00:17:47,403 --> 00:17:48,149
Okay?

268
00:17:51,798 --> 00:17:52,497
Well...

269
00:17:54,096 --> 00:17:55,711
I still like Wayu, you know.

270
00:17:58,118 --> 00:17:59,748
The closer I am to you,

271
00:18:01,689 --> 00:18:03,397
the clearer my feelings get.

272
00:18:05,711 --> 00:18:07,093
I guess

273
00:18:09,391 --> 00:18:11,099
I really can't be just friends with you.

274
00:18:14,717 --> 00:18:15,912
But I'm not trying to pressure you.

275
00:18:17,310 --> 00:18:20,462
I just want you to know
that no matter what,

276
00:18:22,931 --> 00:18:24,328
you'll always have me.

277
00:18:36,347 --> 00:18:37,154
Mind, listen.

278
00:18:38,070 --> 00:18:39,297
I'm sorry.

279
00:18:40,757 --> 00:18:43,614
I do care about you.

280
00:18:45,337 --> 00:18:48,986
But only as a friend.

281
00:18:54,576 --> 00:18:56,440
I still can't forget Captain, Mind.

282
00:18:58,489 --> 00:18:59,467
And...

283
00:19:00,274 --> 00:19:02,150
I don't want to waste anyone's time.

284
00:19:05,632 --> 00:19:08,396
Thank you for always being there for me.

285
00:19:09,871 --> 00:19:10,865
But...

286
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,822
I can only accept it
this way, really, Mind.

287
00:19:15,539 --> 00:19:16,439
I'm sorry.

288
00:19:16,439 --> 00:19:19,793
♪I'll keep loving you
until you see the real world♪

289
00:19:19,793 --> 00:19:22,883
♪And realize it isn't always so perfect♪

290
00:19:22,883 --> 00:19:26,330
♪I'll keep loving you
until you see the real world♪

291
00:19:26,330 --> 00:19:29,653
♪There's still someone like me
who could die in your place♪

292
00:19:29,653 --> 00:19:33,085
♪I'll keep loving you
until you see the real world♪

293
00:19:33,085 --> 00:19:39,512
♪Where a princess
may never find her prince♪

294
00:19:39,653 --> 00:19:45,988
♪Even if you'll never understand me♪

295
00:19:45,988 --> 00:19:52,821
♪Time will show you
that my love is second to none♪

296
00:19:52,821 --> 00:20:00,507
♪Even if you'll never understand me♪

297
00:20:13,938 --> 00:20:16,748
(Thank you for being by my side)

298
00:20:43,379 --> 00:20:44,854
- Hey.
- Huh?

299
00:20:47,587 --> 00:20:50,289
- Did you see Wayu's latest post?
- Yeah.

300
00:20:54,015 --> 00:20:55,910
Looks like he's gone public
with someone named Mind.

301
00:20:59,326 --> 00:21:01,189
I saw them tagging each other
in their stories.

302
00:21:01,888 --> 00:21:03,409
Helping to work on models,

303
00:21:03,953 --> 00:21:05,661
and even giving each other rides home.

304
00:21:09,667 --> 00:21:11,189
And today they even went out
to eat together.

305
00:21:16,950 --> 00:21:18,720
If you still love Wayu,

306
00:21:20,288 --> 00:21:21,779
then go back to him.

307
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:26,732
Apologize, and explain
everything to him.

308
00:21:27,291 --> 00:21:29,651
Whatever he says, just accept it.

309
00:21:31,173 --> 00:21:33,844
That's better than showing up
at my bar drunk every day.

310
00:21:37,229 --> 00:21:38,471
I want to do that too.

311
00:21:40,676 --> 00:21:42,726
You know, I've imagined it
hundreds of times.

312
00:21:43,564 --> 00:21:45,117
How am I supposed to apologize to Wayu?

313
00:21:50,070 --> 00:21:51,297
But there's no way, right?

314
00:21:53,114 --> 00:21:54,635
If I were still with Wayu,

315
00:21:56,079 --> 00:21:57,384
my dad wouldn't stay out of it.

316
00:21:58,533 --> 00:22:00,163
And you know what my dad's capable of.

317
00:22:05,334 --> 00:22:06,700
I don't want him
getting dragged into it.

318
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:10,753
He deserves someone better.

319
00:22:17,104 --> 00:22:21,234
Man, your life's like
a full-on drama series.

320
00:22:26,886 --> 00:22:27,632
Mm.

321
00:22:48,252 --> 00:22:49,619
So? How's it going?

322
00:22:51,187 --> 00:22:52,103
Mm.

323
00:22:54,029 --> 00:22:56,762
How's Mint, the minister's daughter?

324
00:22:56,762 --> 00:22:58,266
You've met her a few times now,
haven't you?

325
00:22:59,556 --> 00:23:01,668
It's... going okay.

326
00:23:02,243 --> 00:23:04,044
What do you mean by "going okay"?

327
00:23:05,053 --> 00:23:07,677
You should bring up marriage
while you have the chance.

328
00:23:07,755 --> 00:23:09,168
I'll talk to them myself later.

329
00:23:12,134 --> 00:23:14,944
- Here's your coffee.
- Ah, thanks.

330
00:23:15,892 --> 00:23:19,370
Come on. They've only been
dating for a month.

331
00:23:19,401 --> 00:23:21,171
You're already talking about marriage?

332
00:23:22,273 --> 00:23:23,749
Why wait any longer?

333
00:23:23,904 --> 00:23:25,581
We should talk about it now.

334
00:23:25,767 --> 00:23:28,547
Krit's at the age where he should
be starting a family.

335
00:23:33,469 --> 00:23:34,214
Yes.

336
00:23:35,317 --> 00:23:37,460
I'll try talking to Mint about marriage.

337
00:23:38,981 --> 00:23:39,742
Good.

338
00:23:40,472 --> 00:23:43,515
And how's that trafficking case
of yours going?

339
00:23:44,804 --> 00:23:47,863
You caught the culprit already.
Why isn't the case closed?

340
00:23:49,028 --> 00:23:50,332
People are still dying.

341
00:23:52,413 --> 00:23:53,593
I can't close it yet.

342
00:23:53,997 --> 00:23:55,332
Not until I'm sure

343
00:23:55,332 --> 00:23:57,071
we can wipe them out completely.

344
00:23:57,071 --> 00:24:00,503
Oh? And you're sure it's the same case?

345
00:24:01,170 --> 00:24:03,282
It could be a copycat.

346
00:24:03,841 --> 00:24:07,009
Trafficking cases like this
have always been around.

347
00:24:08,111 --> 00:24:11,776
The longer you drag this out, the more
people will say you're incompetent.

348
00:24:13,065 --> 00:24:14,478
Just close the case.

349
00:24:15,316 --> 00:24:16,729
Before it turns into a problem.

350
00:24:25,999 --> 00:24:28,794
Grandma will take you today, okay?

351
00:24:28,841 --> 00:24:32,707
Mom's busy with work. I'll pick you up
like usual this evening.

352
00:24:33,903 --> 00:24:35,083
Papa...

353
00:24:36,698 --> 00:24:38,716
- Hmm?
- Papa.

354
00:24:39,563 --> 00:24:40,741
Papa.

355
00:24:41,232 --> 00:24:44,493
Why? Do you miss Papa, dear?

356
00:24:44,493 --> 00:24:47,578
Mm, but don't let Dad hear that.

357
00:24:47,578 --> 00:24:49,175
He might get sad.

358
00:24:50,486 --> 00:24:53,499
Papa is... at... school.

359
00:24:54,570 --> 00:24:57,443
- Huh?
- Papa is at school.

360
00:24:58,499 --> 00:25:00,688
Papa is at school, dear?

361
00:25:01,946 --> 00:25:04,632
Did Papa come to see you
at school, dear?

362
00:25:07,970 --> 00:25:10,222
Then... Then you should go to school.

363
00:25:10,222 --> 00:25:11,588
Grandma will take you today.

364
00:25:12,116 --> 00:25:16,480
Where's your bag? Here it is.
Put it on slowly.

365
00:25:18,032 --> 00:25:20,625
Very good. Now the other side.

366
00:25:28,482 --> 00:25:30,889
- I'm heading out, Wayu.
- See you.

367
00:25:51,324 --> 00:25:52,411
Hello, Tai.

368
00:25:53,870 --> 00:25:55,486
Mind just disappeared.

369
00:25:55,796 --> 00:25:58,358
Should I call him, or go find him?

370
00:25:58,358 --> 00:26:00,268
No, don't.

371
00:26:00,563 --> 00:26:02,240
The more you do this,

372
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:04,724
the more it'll feel like
you're giving him hope.

373
00:26:05,097 --> 00:26:07,162
You need to learn to be
a little cruel sometimes.

374
00:26:07,302 --> 00:26:11,323
Come on, I've already broken his heart twice.
How much crueler do I need to be?

375
00:26:12,302 --> 00:26:14,569
Yeah, fair point.

376
00:26:16,137 --> 00:26:17,705
If I were like Mind,

377
00:26:18,777 --> 00:26:20,749
I probably wouldn't want to see
your face right now.

378
00:26:22,006 --> 00:26:23,870
I think you should give him
some time and space.

379
00:26:26,059 --> 00:26:27,115
Or...

380
00:26:27,519 --> 00:26:30,019
Are you changing your mind,
starting to feel for Mind?

381
00:26:30,019 --> 00:26:31,649
Hey, no.

382
00:26:31,835 --> 00:26:33,994
I'm just feeling lonely.

383
00:26:33,994 --> 00:26:36,680
Normally, he's always around.

384
00:26:36,835 --> 00:26:39,755
And my peers

385
00:26:40,189 --> 00:26:43,869
are all waiting to graduate.
I'm not close with my junior friends either.

386
00:26:43,869 --> 00:26:45,935
Hey, then come to the bar.

387
00:26:45,935 --> 00:26:47,612
Guarantee you won't be lonely.

388
00:26:48,186 --> 00:26:50,857
Let me see first
because I have to submit my project.

389
00:26:50,857 --> 00:26:52,611
Not sure if it'll pass or not.

390
00:26:52,782 --> 00:26:56,043
Okay, if you come, just let me know.

391
00:26:56,571 --> 00:26:57,285
Yeah.

392
00:27:03,791 --> 00:27:07,549
Darn, why did I come up here?

393
00:27:08,357 --> 00:27:09,226
Ugh.

394
00:27:54,846 --> 00:27:58,449
- Hey, Wayu.
- Hey, Tai, let me feel your muscles.

395
00:28:00,157 --> 00:28:02,471
Haven't seen you in a while.
Your muscles seem smaller now.

396
00:28:02,471 --> 00:28:04,116
Yeah. I haven't been working out much.

397
00:28:04,116 --> 00:28:07,005
You're solid as ever, buddy.

398
00:28:07,797 --> 00:28:10,234
Go on, get back out there.
We'll talk later.

399
00:28:10,234 --> 00:28:11,275
- Okay, I'm going to perform first.
- Yeah.

400
00:28:11,275 --> 00:28:13,278
- Wait here first.
- Yeah, hurry up.

401
00:28:37,206 --> 00:28:40,016
- I'm here, everyone.
- Hey, Wayu.

402
00:28:40,016 --> 00:28:43,386
You little troublemaker. Haha.

403
00:28:44,706 --> 00:28:46,010
I missed you so much.

404
00:28:47,873 --> 00:28:49,799
Your muscles are crushing my neck.

405
00:28:49,799 --> 00:28:51,786
Oh, sorry, kid.

406
00:28:51,786 --> 00:28:53,894
Guess I got a little too jacked.

407
00:28:54,706 --> 00:28:58,572
- Darn it.
- You really vanished on us.

408
00:28:58,572 --> 00:29:02,061
Seriously, though, how's school?
You graduating yet?

409
00:29:02,299 --> 00:29:04,830
Come on, it's only been a month.
How would I be graduating already?

410
00:29:05,233 --> 00:29:07,950
The beginning's always an adjustment.

411
00:29:07,950 --> 00:29:11,724
And I've had assignments to turn in,
so I haven't had much free time.

412
00:29:11,724 --> 00:29:13,898
But whenever I do, I come see you guys.

413
00:29:13,898 --> 00:29:16,584
- Mm.
- Aww, man.

414
00:29:16,584 --> 00:29:18,820
You look even more worn out
than when you worked here.

415
00:29:20,295 --> 00:29:22,329
Or are you heartbroken over that cop?

416
00:29:23,929 --> 00:29:26,491
Hey. What? Who's heartbroken?

417
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:29,425
- He, obviously.
- He's just busy. Weren't you listening?

418
00:29:29,425 --> 00:29:33,493
- I did hear him.
- Hey, take it easy.

419
00:29:34,891 --> 00:29:37,500
Then how about a drink
to take the edge off? My treat.

420
00:29:37,500 --> 00:29:38,602
Come on.

421
00:29:40,062 --> 00:29:43,727
No, thanks, Foei. I'm not really
in the mood to drink lately.

422
00:29:47,515 --> 00:29:51,816
Then how about going on stage?
Since you're already here.

423
00:29:53,198 --> 00:29:57,034
Yeah, just do a set. Nothing serious.

424
00:29:58,726 --> 00:30:01,304
I can't, Foei.
I haven't practiced at all.

425
00:30:01,661 --> 00:30:03,804
- I won't make it.
- Oh, come on.

426
00:30:03,804 --> 00:30:05,481
You'll manage just fine.

427
00:30:05,527 --> 00:30:07,406
Even if you forgot the moves,

428
00:30:07,888 --> 00:30:10,124
just show off
that handsome face of yours,

429
00:30:10,124 --> 00:30:12,574
and let the customers look at you.
That's all you need to do.

430
00:30:12,574 --> 00:30:13,958
Yeah, bro, enjoy.

431
00:30:13,958 --> 00:30:16,272
No big deal. Come dance with us.

432
00:30:16,272 --> 00:30:17,748
- Yeah.
- Come on, Wayu, trust us.

433
00:30:17,748 --> 00:30:20,682
Get out on the floor
and the crowd will go wild.

434
00:30:20,745 --> 00:30:22,142
Come on.

435
00:30:22,158 --> 00:30:30,340
Wayu!

436
00:30:30,340 --> 00:30:31,505
Okay!

437
00:30:32,421 --> 00:30:33,337
Fine, I'll do it.

438
00:32:38,227 --> 00:32:39,919
Let's invite our guests.

439
00:32:39,919 --> 00:32:43,643
Feel free to garland the boys
and tip them.

440
00:32:43,643 --> 00:32:45,525
- From the back, please.
- Thank you.

441
00:32:55,944 --> 00:32:56,720
So?

442
00:32:58,537 --> 00:32:59,251
Settle it.

443
00:32:59,965 --> 00:33:01,906
Thank you so much.

444
00:33:02,388 --> 00:33:04,406
- Oh, hello, Ice.
- Hello.

445
00:33:04,406 --> 00:33:08,365
If this is your type, Mr. Ice,
may I recommend Kenji?

446
00:33:08,365 --> 00:33:10,438
He may look a little nerdy,

447
00:33:10,438 --> 00:33:12,605
but he's caring and attentive.

448
00:33:13,443 --> 00:33:14,934
I'm booking Wayu for 500 drinks.

449
00:33:14,934 --> 00:33:16,269
500 drinks? Seriously?

450
00:33:18,863 --> 00:33:19,670
Wayu.

451
00:33:22,682 --> 00:33:25,757
- Hey, Ice.
- How've you been? Long time no see.

452
00:33:25,990 --> 00:33:28,148
- Doing well?
- I'm good.

453
00:33:28,148 --> 00:33:29,685
Come on. Have a drink with me.

454
00:33:31,999 --> 00:33:34,872
- Uh, well...
- Wayu, just take it.

455
00:33:34,872 --> 00:33:36,393
He booked you for 500 drinks.

456
00:33:38,427 --> 00:33:41,207
Alright then, I'll have Wayu
look after you tonight, Mr. Ice.

457
00:33:41,207 --> 00:33:42,604
- Thank you so much.
- Sure.

458
00:33:42,604 --> 00:33:44,281
What are you hesitating for? Go on.

459
00:33:44,281 --> 00:33:46,145
- Just a little bit.
- I'm coming.

460
00:33:46,533 --> 00:33:48,210
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

461
00:33:48,210 --> 00:33:49,390
Need more ice?

462
00:33:49,390 --> 00:33:50,694
- Yeah, a bit.
- Okay.

463
00:33:58,101 --> 00:33:59,203
Thank you.

464
00:34:05,073 --> 00:34:08,365
- Come on. Let's toast to both of us.
- Sure.

465
00:34:13,241 --> 00:34:16,113
Don't like this drink?
You can change it.

466
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:18,349
- Oh, no worries.
- Hey, man.

467
00:34:18,349 --> 00:34:19,296
No.

468
00:34:19,529 --> 00:34:21,796
I haven't had a drink in over a month.

469
00:34:21,796 --> 00:34:24,079
So getting back into it,
I'm a little out of practice.

470
00:34:24,079 --> 00:34:26,967
Oh? Why's that? Were you sick?

471
00:34:27,060 --> 00:34:28,628
No, not really. Uh...

472
00:34:29,001 --> 00:34:32,184
I went back to school,
so I don't come here much anymore.

473
00:34:32,184 --> 00:34:34,979
Ah, that explains it. No wonder
I haven't seen you around.

474
00:34:36,144 --> 00:34:38,162
Guess I'm lucky today,
getting to see you.

475
00:34:38,162 --> 00:34:39,575
Wow, I'm lucky too.

476
00:34:39,700 --> 00:34:42,557
You know, Ice, if it were anyone else,

477
00:34:42,883 --> 00:34:44,544
- I wouldn't accept it.
- Wow.

478
00:34:44,979 --> 00:34:46,811
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

479
00:34:50,057 --> 00:34:52,029
It's alright. You don't have to drink.

480
00:34:52,246 --> 00:34:53,380
Just chatting is enough.

481
00:34:53,814 --> 00:34:57,836
No way. When I take a job,
I have to give it my all.

482
00:34:57,836 --> 00:35:00,600
- Hmm.
- Then how about this?

483
00:35:01,019 --> 00:35:04,450
Whoever finishes last does a shot.

484
00:35:05,988 --> 00:35:07,541
- You said it.
- Mmm.

485
00:35:07,572 --> 00:35:09,575
- Deal.
- Come on.

486
00:35:10,289 --> 00:35:11,050
Go!

487
00:35:15,103 --> 00:35:17,836
I win. Shot.

488
00:35:18,550 --> 00:35:19,854
One Ferris wheel, please.

489
00:35:37,432 --> 00:35:39,419
Whoa.

490
00:35:39,994 --> 00:35:43,969
- Ice, you're better at dancing.
- Just a little.

491
00:35:45,723 --> 00:35:49,823
Hey, I have to go.
My customer's calling.

492
00:35:49,823 --> 00:35:51,702
Okay, see you.

493
00:35:56,344 --> 00:35:57,556
Want to keep this going somewhere else?

494
00:35:58,223 --> 00:35:59,931
Uh...

495
00:36:01,872 --> 00:36:04,372
Hey, be back by 4 AM, okay?

496
00:36:04,527 --> 00:36:05,692
Please.

497
00:36:05,692 --> 00:36:06,857
- Okay.
- Sure.

498
00:36:06,857 --> 00:36:08,534
Excuse me, could we get
the check, please?

499
00:36:10,863 --> 00:36:13,611
Bottoms up!

500
00:36:15,521 --> 00:36:19,294
Wow. Done already?

501
00:36:19,294 --> 00:36:21,173
Yay.

502
00:36:23,114 --> 00:36:25,723
Wait, Ice. I've got this.

503
00:36:26,002 --> 00:36:28,580
Thank you. Uh... Haha... Oh.

504
00:36:37,664 --> 00:36:39,837
Hey, thank you, bro.

505
00:36:39,837 --> 00:36:41,406
Thank you, bro. You too, bro.

506
00:36:41,406 --> 00:36:42,477
Okay, go.

507
00:36:45,117 --> 00:36:46,219
Mm.

508
00:36:48,580 --> 00:36:50,660
Great. Come on.

509
00:36:56,297 --> 00:36:58,905
Oh, oops.

510
00:37:01,777 --> 00:37:05,426
Oh.

511
00:37:06,980 --> 00:37:09,138
- Hold on.
- What's up?

512
00:37:09,138 --> 00:37:11,747
- Hey.
- Whoa.

513
00:37:12,508 --> 00:37:13,626
Hold on, Ice.

514
00:37:14,138 --> 00:37:15,831
- This one's pretty good.
- Really?

515
00:37:18,268 --> 00:37:19,216
Mm.

516
00:37:28,128 --> 00:37:31,648
Come on, come on! Woo-hoo!

517
00:37:34,656 --> 00:37:36,864
Go, go, go!

518
00:37:46,810 --> 00:37:55,578
(Thai police are dedicated
to public safety)

519
00:38:03,733 --> 00:38:04,852
That's enough for today.

520
00:38:05,783 --> 00:38:06,886
Go home and get some rest.

521
00:38:09,665 --> 00:38:10,302
Sergeant.

522
00:38:12,305 --> 00:38:14,634
- Sergeant.
- Uh, yeah, sir.

523
00:38:15,131 --> 00:38:16,156
Go home and sleep.

524
00:38:18,081 --> 00:38:19,432
I can handle it, Captain.

525
00:38:21,979 --> 00:38:23,190
Let's call it a day.

526
00:38:24,059 --> 00:38:28,080
In the morning, I'll go follow up
with the latest victim's family.

527
00:38:29,090 --> 00:38:30,227
Have them coordinate it.

528
00:38:31,062 --> 00:38:34,137
Yes, sir. But it'll
be morning soon, Captain.

529
00:38:34,137 --> 00:38:36,124
You should take care
of yourself too, Captain.

530
00:38:36,979 --> 00:38:37,724
I can't.

531
00:38:38,842 --> 00:38:40,456
I'm being pressured to close the case.

532
00:38:41,792 --> 00:38:43,842
We need to find
the real culprit, and fast.

533
00:38:45,596 --> 00:38:47,522
But Por still won't talk.

534
00:38:48,189 --> 00:38:50,891
Should we lean on him again?
Make him talk?

535
00:38:53,795 --> 00:38:56,108
It won't work. I've already tried.

536
00:38:57,723 --> 00:38:58,329
Let's go.

537
00:39:01,062 --> 00:39:04,649
Captain! Look at this, Captain.

538
00:39:07,847 --> 00:39:11,916
I found a clip of our victim on the dark web.

539
00:39:12,537 --> 00:39:14,990
There are a lot of them, actually.
Take a look, Captain.

540
00:39:20,518 --> 00:39:23,127
Can we find out who uploaded it?

541
00:39:24,089 --> 00:39:26,682
It might take a little time,
but I'll try.

542
00:39:33,818 --> 00:39:34,842
(Typing codes)

543
00:39:39,994 --> 00:39:41,913
Sigh, Ugh.

544
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:03,078
Whoa.

545
00:40:06,154 --> 00:40:08,265
What are you doing, huh?

546
00:40:08,747 --> 00:40:09,632
What are you doing?

547
00:40:10,486 --> 00:40:13,607
Help! Someone, help!

548
00:40:14,011 --> 00:40:15,827
- Help.
- Haha.

549
00:40:16,480 --> 00:40:18,824
- Help.
- Shh.

550
00:40:20,222 --> 00:40:22,116
No one can hear you scream.

551
00:40:23,452 --> 00:40:25,330
Because there's only you and me here.

552
00:40:27,194 --> 00:40:29,740
Hey, who are you?

553
00:40:34,103 --> 00:40:34,864
Hello.

554
00:40:37,131 --> 00:40:37,877
Ice.

555
00:40:41,852 --> 00:40:43,420
You're not getting away from me.

556
00:40:49,165 --> 00:40:51,231
I've played along
with your game long enough.

557
00:40:52,240 --> 00:40:54,522
Now it's your turn to play mine.

558
00:40:58,606 --> 00:41:01,060
Ice, get out of here if you don't want
to get dragged into this.

559
00:41:01,976 --> 00:41:03,109
Run? Okay.

560
00:41:04,957 --> 00:41:06,339
Can I borrow the whip?

561
00:41:06,836 --> 00:41:08,310
- Sure.
- Mind if I borrow this?

562
00:41:08,310 --> 00:41:08,948
Okay.

563
00:41:39,506 --> 00:41:41,494
Ice, um...

564
00:41:42,891 --> 00:41:44,817
If you want the video to turn out good,

565
00:41:45,251 --> 00:41:47,223
I think you should untie me.

566
00:41:48,062 --> 00:41:49,304
I promise,

567
00:41:49,692 --> 00:41:51,928
I'll make sure it's a knockout.

568
00:41:54,211 --> 00:41:55,764
If you want something satisfying,

569
00:41:57,239 --> 00:41:58,854
you'll have to do better than this.

570
00:42:16,858 --> 00:42:19,642
(Emergency number)

571
00:42:26,477 --> 00:42:27,549
This one's better.

572
00:42:38,278 --> 00:42:39,132
Found it.

573
00:42:41,772 --> 00:42:43,077
It's in Malaysia.

574
00:42:43,511 --> 00:42:44,598
Malaysia, huh?

575
00:42:47,222 --> 00:42:50,328
Chainphop has many clients
from Malaysia.

576
00:42:52,642 --> 00:42:54,272
Try to find it first.

577
00:43:01,290 --> 00:43:03,542
Arvo, the company's called Arvo.

578
00:43:03,542 --> 00:43:05,467
Arvo.

579
00:43:11,026 --> 00:43:12,129
Mm.

580
00:43:14,598 --> 00:43:15,343
Got it.

581
00:43:23,262 --> 00:43:24,132
Found it.

582
00:43:25,684 --> 00:43:29,582
(Irfan Faruhanan, Malaysia)
The owner is Irfan Faruhanan.

583
00:43:37,178 --> 00:43:39,578
(Crown Plaza Hotel Bangkok, Lumpini Park,
4.4 stars, 2682, Five-star hotel)

584
00:43:44,250 --> 00:43:46,426
(First spotted in Silom)

585
00:43:54,100 --> 00:43:54,954
Found him.

586
00:43:56,507 --> 00:43:57,221
Lieutenant.

587
00:43:57,827 --> 00:44:00,327
Check whether Irfan is in Thailand.

588
00:44:00,327 --> 00:44:02,237
Find out how many houses, condos,
and warehouses he has.

589
00:44:02,237 --> 00:44:04,147
Wherever they are,
get warrants for all of them.

590
00:44:04,317 --> 00:44:05,389
Yes, Captain.

591
00:44:50,062 --> 00:44:52,500
Everyone, gear up.
I've got the suspect's location.

592
00:44:52,531 --> 00:44:55,279
Sergeant, call for backup now.
I already sent the coordinates.

593
00:44:55,729 --> 00:44:57,857
- Everyone got that?
- Yes, sir.

594
00:45:01,754 --> 00:45:02,670
Haha.

595
00:45:04,751 --> 00:45:06,723
Such a good boy, hmm?

596
00:45:07,282 --> 00:45:09,658
- Ah.
- Hmm?

597
00:45:13,726 --> 00:45:14,937
So...

598
00:45:16,490 --> 00:45:19,922
If I run, I die.
If I stay, I die anyway.

599
00:45:20,372 --> 00:45:23,353
So I might as well enjoy this.

600
00:45:49,098 --> 00:45:52,887
Ice, if you want this to be good,

601
00:45:54,626 --> 00:45:56,179
you should untie me first.

602
00:45:57,918 --> 00:45:58,787
Sound good?

603
00:46:01,722 --> 00:46:02,483
Mm.

604
00:46:04,672 --> 00:46:08,384
You're the first one
who I've ever untied.

605
00:46:49,842 --> 00:46:52,855
- I'll make it worth your while.
- Okay.

606
00:46:52,855 --> 00:46:55,231
Okay, come here.

607
00:47:31,519 --> 00:47:32,295
You...

608
00:49:13,769 --> 00:49:15,803
You're not getting away from me.

609
00:49:24,746 --> 00:49:25,460
Hey!

610
00:49:40,864 --> 00:49:42,215
You're finished, Irfan.

611
00:49:54,172 --> 00:49:55,552
It's okay.

612
00:50:01,361 --> 00:50:02,991
Hold on. Come here.

613
00:50:06,842 --> 00:50:08,302
- Are you alright?
- I'm fine.

614
00:50:08,302 --> 00:50:09,808
Krit, be careful, Krit.

615
00:50:23,255 --> 00:50:25,351
Can you manage? Let me help.

616
00:50:27,075 --> 00:50:28,534
- Are you alright?
- I'm fine.

617
00:50:29,419 --> 00:50:31,235
Just a moment. Let's go.

618
00:50:31,547 --> 00:50:33,752
- You okay?
- I'm okay.

619
